{"id":"project-LICHEN-nmbu","title":"dodag.c: select_parent hysteresis ignores current parent admissibility","description":"File: lichen/subsys/lichen/rpl/dodag.c:242-258

In lichen_rpl_dodag_select_parent(), the hysteresis logic compares the current parent's cost against the best admissible candidate but doesn't verify that the current parent itself is still admissible.

The code at line 242-258:
```c
if (d->has_preferred_parent && !rpl_addr_eq(d->preferred_parent, best_addr)) {
    struct lichen_rpl_parent *cur = find_parent(d, d->preferred_parent);
    if (cur != NULL) {
        uint16_t cur_cost = path_cost(cur, mhri);
        if ((uint32_t)best_cost + (uint32_t)threshold >= (uint32_t)cur_cost) {
            /* Not enough improvement - stay with current */
            chosen_addr = cur->addr;
            chosen_cost = cur_cost;
        }
    }
}
```

If the current parent's rank increased (e.g., from a DIO with higher rank), it could become inadmissible (path_cost > lowest_rank + max_rank_increase) while still being valid in the parent list. The hysteresis check would still prefer staying with it if the improvement doesn't exceed threshold.

This violates RFC 6550 Section 8.2.2.4: 'A node MUST NOT increase its own rank beyond a ceiling value DAGMaxRankIncrease + cur_min_path_cost'.

Fix: Add is_admissible(d, cur) check before applying hysteresis:
```c
if (cur != NULL && is_admissible(d, cur)) {
    // ... hysteresis logic
}
